  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0b95\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc2\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc6\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0ba4\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Presidential resolution to end the parliamentary session",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "President Ranil Wickramasinghe has decided to end the parliamentary session. Opposition leader Korada Laxman Kiriella said that he informed the party leaders about this.",
        "President Ranil Wickremesinghe is having a discussion with the party leaders after taking the oath of office at the Parliament complex today. At the same time, he mentioned that the parliamentary session will be adjourned for one day.",
        "However, Lakshman Kiriella said that it has not been announced on which date the parliamentary session will be postponed.",
        "Parliament finally convened yesterday Wednesday and after the election of the President, Speaker Mahinda Yappa Abeywardana adjourned Parliament until 10 am on the 27th. According to it, the Parliament should meet on the 27th. But the president can adjourn the parliamentary session at any time, which is the power vested in the president in the constitution.",
        "However, now that Ranil Wickramasinghe has assumed office as the new president, it has been decided to postpone the second session of the 9th Parliament by one day and start the third session in a formal manner so that the president can start the parliamentary session on a formal basis. But it has not been confirmed whether it will be adjourned after Parliament convenes on the 27th or before that, said Opposition Prime Minister Korada Lakshman Kiriella.",
        "Meanwhile, Parliament is being convened on the 27th to seek the approval of the Parliament for the emergency law. Therefore, it is expected that the parliamentary session will be adjourned by the President after the 27th."
      ],
